Prepare macaroni and cheese according to package directions. Fold in eggs. Spread into a greased 13-in. x 9-in. x 2-in. baking dish. Top with pizza sauce, pepperoni and mozzarella. Bake, uncovered, at 350 degrees F for 30-35 minutes or until lightly browned and cheese is melted. Let stand for 5 minutes before serving.